  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Traditional architectural-shingle brown. Camelot Ii Weathered Timber is a workhorse color on craftsman, traditional, and Tudor-style homes where the roof is meant to grow out of the landscape rather than contrast against it. The granule blend uses warm tobacco and weathered-wood accents to keep the surface visually alive.",
      "Look closely and you can pick out three or four granule shades inside the blend. The eye stops registering them at conversational distance, but the layered texture is why warm-brown asphalt roofs photograph as 'rich' rather than 'flat'.",
      "Difficult to use poorly on a craftsman, traditional, or Tudor home. Harder to specify on a stark modern build where the warmth of the roof can fight the rest of the palette."
    ],
